  "text": "Measurements were made according to the criteria published by the American Society of Echocardiography [CITATION_1] . Patients were examined in the left lateral decubitus position using a commercially available system (Vivid 7, GE Healthcare, Horten, Norway). A 3.5-MHz transducer was used to obtain images and was focused at a depth of 16 cm in the parasternal 115 and apical views (standard long-axis and two-and four-chamber images).",
